QuizName: Can you finish these lyrics from Taylor Swift's Lover Album?
QuizDescription: It just matches this websites aesthetic so well!!!
QuizTags: Taylor Swift, music, lyrics, lover album, song vibes

QuestionName: You hold my hand on the street...
1: ...I turned around before I hit the tunnel
3: ...I thought you were leading me on
Lesson:
You hold my hand on the street
Walk me back to that apartment
Years ago, we were just inside
Barefoot in the kitchen
Sacred new beginnings
That became my religion, listen
~Cornelia Street (Track 9)

QuestionName: Ladies and gentlemen, will you please stand?
1: With every guitar string scar on my hand
2: I've loved you three summers now, honey, but I want 'em all
3: Swear to be overdramatic and true to my lover
4: I take this magnetic force of a man to be my lover
Lesson:
Ladies and gentlemen, will you please stand?
With every guitar string scar on my hand
I take this magnetic force of a man to be my lover
My heart's been borrowed and yours has been blue
All's well that ends well to end up with you
Swear to be overdramatic and true to my lover
~Lover (Track 3)

QuestionName: "I love you, " ain't that the worst thing you ever heard?
1: He looks so pretty like a devil
2: I'm drunk in the back of the car
3: Devils roll the dice, angels roll their eyes
4: He looks up grinning like a devil
5: What doesn't kill me makes me want you more
Lesson:
And I snuck in through the garden gate
Every night that summer just to seal my fate (oh)
And I screamed for whatever it's worth
"I love you, " ain't that the worst thing you ever heard?
He looks up grinning like a devil
~Cruel Summer (Track 2)

QuestionName: And obsessin' 'bout somebody else is no fun
1: And I ain't trying mess with your self-expression
2: Like, can you just not step on his gown?
3: And snakes and stones never broke my bones so
4: And shade never made anybody less gay so
Lesson:
And I ain't trying mess with your self-expression
But I've learned the lesson that stressin'
And obsessin' 'bout somebody else is no fun
And snakes and stones never broke my bones so
~You Need To Calm Down (Track 14)

QuestionName: But something happened, I heard him laughing...
1: ...They say home is where the heart is
2: ...Took me back to Highgate, met all of his best mates
3: ...I got drunk and made fun of the way you talk
5: ...I saw the dimples first and then I heard the accent
Lesson:
I love my hometown as much as Motown, I love SoCal
And you know I love Springsteen, faded blue jeans, Tennessee whiskey
But something happened, I heard him laughing
I saw the dimples first and then I heard the accent
They say home is where the heart is
But that's not where mine lives
~London Boy (Track 11)

QuestionName: What I was wearing, If I was rude...
1: ...And I'm so sick of them coming at me again
2: ...Could all be separated from my good ideas and power moves?
3: ...Wondering if I'd get there quicker If I was a man
4: ...I'd be a fearless leader, I'd be an alpha type
Lesson:
They'd say I hustled
Put in the work
They wouldn't shake their heads and question how much of this I deserve
What I was wearing
If I was rude
Could all be separated from my good ideas and power moves?
~The Man (Track 4)

QuestionName: They whisper in the hallway, "she's a bad, bad girl"...
1: ...The whole school is rolling fake dice
2: ...Voted most likely to run away with you
4: ....It's you and me, That's my whole world
Lesson:
It's you and me
That's my whole world
They whisper in the hallway, "she's a bad, bad girl" (okay!)
The whole school is rolling fake dice
You play stupid games, you win stupid prizes
~Miss Americana & the Heartbreak Prince (Track 7)

QuestionName: And I cut off my nose just to spite my face...
1: ... and you bite your face to spite your nose
3: ...And all of my heroes die all alone
4: ...Then I hate my reflection for years and years
Lesson:
Dark side, I search for your dark side
But what if I'm alright, right, right, right here?
And I cut off my nose just to spite my face
Then I hate my reflection for years and years
~The Archer (Track 5)
